  <static seed="127" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring425.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{x^{2}y^{2}-7x^{2}yz-8x^{2}z^{2}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x^{2}\mathopen{}\left(y+z\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-8z\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Let<rsq/>s start by noting that <m>x^2</m> is common to each term, so 
we may write</p>
<p><m>{x^{2}y^{2}-7x^{2}yz-8x^{2}z^{2}}={x^{2}\mathopen{}\left(y^{2}-7yz-8z^{2}\right)}</m></p>
<p>To factor the expression further we make the following observations:
<ul label="disc">
<li>
<p>the leading coefficient is 1</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the last term<rsq/>s coefficient is <em>negative</em> which means that the factorization will 
have one of the following forms</p>
<p><m>(y-\mathbf{?}z)(y+\mathbf{?}z), (y+\mathbf{?}z)(y-\mathbf{?}z)</m></p>
</li>
</ul></p>
<p>We look for factors of <m>-8</m> that add to <m>-7</m>; the 
factors that work are <m>1</m> and <m>-8</m> so</p>
<p><m>{x^{2}y^{2}-7x^{2}yz-8x^{2}z^{2}}={x^{2}\mathopen{}\left(y+z\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-8z\right)}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
